$ Windows: Primary/Secondary Monitor - Resolution etc.

→ Windows supports multiple connected monitors.

{ Primary monitor #primary-monitory

  If more than one monitor is connected, one of these monitors is the *primary monitor*.

  The primary monitor is the monitor where Windows will display some interesting things, for example, when
  using alt-tabulator to cycle over the running applications.

}
{ Change settings

  Monitor setting, such as choosing the primary monitor or screen resolution can be changed by typing
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/desk_cpl[`desk.cpl`] in a command line.

}
